OL,3,CUS actor in legal battle with council
OL,4,Cto gain control of his ancestral home
OL,6,FIn his witness statement, he said: "I
OL,7,Fwould not have given up my life in the
OL,8,FUS, left my family and friends behind,
OL,9,Fto move to a new country and invest my
OL,10,Fpersonal savings if physical works
OL,11,Fpermissions and listed building
OL,12,Fapprovals had been part of the
OL,13,Fobligation before I owned Hopwood
OL,14,FHall."
OL,16,FHe said that at the time of the
OL,17,Fagreement in 2017, the Grade II listed
OL,18,Fbuilding was predicted to become
OL,19,Fruinous within five to 10 years.
OL,26,@nD@dOUvD@FO]
