OL,4,Cto gain control of his ancestral home
OL,6,FThe hall was built in the 1420s by his
OL,7,Fancestors, who lived there for 500
OL,8,Fyears before the property fell out of
OL,9,Fthe family's ownership because its
OL,10,Fheirs were killed in the First World
OL,11,FWar, Mr DePree added.
OL,13,FWhen Mr DePree learned of the hall in
OL,14,F2013, he became concerned about its
OL,15,Fdereliction and committed himself to
OL,16,Frestoring it, he said in court
OL,17,Fdocuments.
OL,19,FHe continued: "From the moment I first
OL,20,Fentered Hopwood Hall in 2013 I was
OL,21,Fimmediately inspired.
OL,26,@{D@OOU
